main event: Mr. Richard Heuther reported a UFO sighting in Hamburg, New York, involving multiple luminous objects observed on February 6, 1969.
interesting points: The objects exhibited erratic, rapid movements and changed direction abruptly., The sighting lasted for approximately 30 minutes and involved three adult witnesses., The objects were described as circular, with sizes ranging from 15 to 25 feet in diameter., The sighting occurred under clear skies with no significant weather conditions., The witnesses reported variations in light intensity from the objects, which made no sound during the observation.
sighted object: multiple distinct luminous objects in the sky
